parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unavailable Recall Repair Parts for Air Bag Recall (NHTSA Campaign Number: 23V334000)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall repair parts for the air bag recall may lead to a potential safety risk, as the faulty air bag system may cause injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: None reported
as the issue is related to the unavailability of recall repair parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of power, inability to shift gears, and sudden acceleration, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or refuses to shift gears
the transmission slips or jerks
the vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
the transmission makes loud clunking or grinding noises
the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping or hesitation can cause loss of power, difficulty shifting gears, and sudden acceleration, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates or slips when shifting gears
the vehicle jerks or lurches forward
the transmission makes loud clunking or grinding noises
the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
the engine revs suddenly
the vehicle surges forward unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission clutch failure can cause loss of power, difficulty shifting gears, and sudden acceleration, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission clutch housing is damaged
the 3-5-R clutch housing is faulty
metal debris is found in the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause discomfort and inconvenience to the driver and passengers, particularly in hot climates.
symptoms: The air conditioner stops working
fails to blow cold air
or produces warm air.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The issues with the fuel system and engine can cause gas fumes to leak into the cabin, posing a risk of fire or health problems for the occupants.
symptoms: Gas fumes coming out of the A/C vents
fuel injector or cracked head issues
strong fuel odor inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the SSDS can cause the system light to stay on, which can be distracting and annoying to the driver, and may also lead to unnecessary repairs.
symptoms: Service side detection system light stays on and will not turn off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the collision alert system can increase the risk of accidents, as the system may not provide timely warnings to the driver.
symptoms: Collision alert system does not work consistently
fails to signal when approaching a slowing vehicle.
